---
// src/pages/projects/biomed-instrumentation.astro
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Biomedical Instrumentation | Ean Cummings">
  <article class="project-deep-dive animate-fade-in">
    
    <!-- 1. CINEMATIC HEADER -->
    <header class="project-hero">
      <div class="project-hero-container">
        <span class="pro-tag-badge">Biomedical Systems Engineering</span>
        <h1 class="pro-headline">ECG Data Acquisition</h1>
        <p class="pro-subheading">
          A bespoke instrumentation system designed for cardiac signal acquisition, featuring a multi-stage analog filter topology and digital peak-detection algorithms.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-overlay"></div>
    </header>

    <!-- 2. ANALOG FRONTEND -->
    <section class="pro-content-row">
      <div class="pro-sidebar">
        <span class="row-num">01 / Analog Frontend</span>
        <h2>Instrumentation & Filtering</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="pro-main-body">
        <p>
          The system's integrity relies on a high-gain instrumentation amplifier (gain approximately 1000 V/V) configured to isolate cardiac micro-volt signals from common-mode noise. The signal chain incorporates a low-pass filter (cutoff 250 Hz) and a high-pass filter (cutoff 0.03 Hz) to isolate the QRS complex while eliminating baseline wander and high-frequency interference.
        </p>
        <p>
          To ensure subject safety and signal clarity, I implemented a <strong>Driven Right Leg (DRL) circuit</strong>, which effectively minimizes common-mode interference by actively canceling body-coupled noise.
        </p>

        <!-- Media Gallery -->
        <div class="product-media-gallery">
          <div class="media-panel-box">
            <img src="/images/ekg-schematic.png" alt="Instrumentation Amplifier Schematic" class="media-photo" />
            <span class="media-caption">Instrumentation amplifier schematic utilizing precise resistor values to achieve a target gain of 1000 V/V.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="media-panel-box">
            <img src="/images/ekg-freq-response.png" alt="Frequency Response Plot" class="media-photo" />
            <span class="media-caption">System frequency response verifying filter cutoff accuracy and consistent gain performance.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 3. DIGITAL PIPELINE -->
    <section class="pro-content-row">
      <div class="pro-sidebar">
        <span class="row-num">02 / Digital Pipeline</span>
        <h2>DSP & Peak Detection</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="pro-main-body">
        <p>
          To process the raw signal, I designed a real-time digital signal processing pipeline running on an Arduino platform. A <strong>60 Hz notch filter</strong>—mathematically modeled with MATLAB coefficients—removes power-line noise, a standard challenge in non-shielded clinical environments.
        </p>
        <p>
          The pipeline utilizes a difference equation for stable filtering, followed by an adaptive peak-detection algorithm that dynamically compares input samples against calculated thresholds. This system accurately computes beats-per-minute (BPM) and provides real-time identification of regular vs. irregular cardiac rhythms based on inter-peak delta-T intervals.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 4. TECH SPECS -->
    <section class="pro-content-row border-top-only">
      <div class="pro-sidebar">
        <span class="row-num">03 / Specs</span>
        <h2>Instrumentation Specs</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="pro-main-body">
        <div class="specs-mini-grid">
          <div class="spec-mini-card">
            <h4>Analog Gain</h4>
            <p>1000 V/V Instrumentation Amplifier Topology</p>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-mini-card">
            <h4>Filtering</h4>
            <p>LPF (250 Hz), HPF (0.03 Hz), 60 Hz Notch</p>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-mini-card">
            <h4>Noise Mitigation</h4>
            <p>Driven Right Leg (DRL) Circuitry</p>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-mini-card">
            <h4>Analysis</h4>
            <p>Real-time Peak Detection & Delta-T Rhythm Analysis</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .project-deep-dive {
    max-width: 1024px;
    width: min(100%, 92%);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 80px 0;
  }

  /* --- Hero Styling --- */
  .project-hero {
    min-height: 45vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .project-hero-container {
    z-index: 10;
  }

  .pro-tag-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--accent-blue);
    background: rgba(47, 128, 237, 0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(47, 128, 237, 0.2);
    border-radius: 100px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .pro-headline {
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: 0 0 16px 0;
    color: var(--text-apple);
  }

  .pro-subheading {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    max-width: 650px;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .grid-overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image: radial-gradient(rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04) 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size: 32px 32px;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  /* --- Row Layout Mechanics --- */
  .pro-content-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 40px;
    padding: 64px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .border-top-only {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .pro-content-row {
      grid-template-columns: 3fr 5fr;
      gap: 64px;
    }
    .pro-sidebar {
      position: sticky;
      top: 100px;
    }
  }

  .row-num {
    font-family: monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .pro-sidebar h2 {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-top: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .pro-main-body {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
  .pro-main-body p {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  /* --- Upgraded Dual Photo Showcase Grid --- */
  .product-media-gallery {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 20px;
    margin-top: 32px;
    width: 100%;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .product-media-gallery {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .media-panel-box {
    background: #0d0d0e;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 20px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .media-photo {
    width: 100%;
    max-height: 240px; 
    object-fit: cover; 
    object-position: top center; 
    border-radius: 8px;
    display: block;
  }

  .media-caption {
    display: block;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-top: 10px;
    padding: 0 4px;
    text-align: left;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  /* --- Technical Spec Breakdown --- */
  .specs-mini-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .spec-mini-card {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.01);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .spec-mini-card h4 {
    margin: 0 0 6px 0;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .spec-mini-card p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }
</style>